it's more like people are scribble shaped. I mean,  

771
01:04:09,120 --> 01:04:13,680
there's the really best people you've worked with, 
they're more like scribbles than they are T-shaped  

772
01:04:13,680 --> 01:04:18,360
because of course you want to be horizontally 
capable, so you want to be broad and you do  

773
01:04:18,360 --> 01:04:22,320
want to be deep, but you actually want to be deep 
in way more than one thing. Now obviously when I  

774
01:04:22,320 --> 01:04:29,760
say deep, I don't mean I'm not able to do the 
job of our finance function all day every day,  

775
01:04:29,760 --> 01:04:36,480
but I'm 100% good enough to go three clicks 
below the simple financial analysis. I can go  

776
01:04:36,480 --> 01:04:41,080
reasonably deep in our financials because I 
want to and because it's partly it matters.  

777
01:04:41,080 --> 01:04:45,040
It's important to be able to do that. And 
so maybe a different way to think about that  

778
01:04:45,040 --> 01:04:51,120
bingo card is I've rarely regretted going 
deep in something that isn't quite my job. 

779
01:04:51,120 --> 01:04:55,200
I've rarely regretted it. The worst case scenario 
is I've learned something new that I will never  

780
01:04:55,200 --> 01:05:00,160
use, which I guess at least that made my 
brain slightly more agile. I don't know,  

781
01:05:00,160 --> 01:05:05,040
there must be some potential benefit of that. 
But the very best case scenario is that when I  

782
01:05:05,040 --> 01:05:09,680
least suspect it at some point in the future it 
will turn out to be the thing that matters. It  

783
01:05:09,680 --> 01:05:14,240
will be the tool that I need, but I'm facing 
some important problem and I will be like,  

784
01:05:14,240 --> 01:05:18,800
"Oh my god, this was worth every cent." And 
so if you think about it on an ROI basis,  

785
01:05:18,800 --> 01:05:22,760
doing things that aren't in your wheelhouse, 
that aren't the things directly in front of you,  

786
01:05:22,760 --> 01:05:26,440
the ROI can really be outlandish. 
It can be off the charts great,  

787
01:05:26,440 --> 01:05:29,640
but I guess it's speculative. Because you 
don't know you're going to need it tomorrow.  

788
01:05:29,640 --> 01:05:33,360
You don't know if it's going to be something 
that's going to be a regular tool you use.

789
01:05:33,360 --> 01:05:36,960
What's interesting is the bingo 
card is the analogy. Is there a  

